    "body": "### Problem\n\nHey, I believe after 0.11 (when the improved buf hover highlighting) came out I started to sometimes notice that treesitter markdown sometimes does not render correctly, if at all.\n\nIn the showcase below please see what happens after 10-30mins of normal editing session (using lsp, navigating, etc...). That's the biggest problem, if I restart nvim at first everything works correctly :/\n\n\n<details>\n\n<summary>Showcase</summary>\n\n```lua\nvim.keymap.set(\"n\", \"<leader>t\", function()\n    vim.lsp.buf.hover({ border = \"rounded\" })\nend)\n```\n\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/6bc43cb2-a802-477d-9763-ec89e637294f\n\n\nSometimes it does not even render at all, but it is possible to make it render, I explained that below:\n\n![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/10f99e3f-0e85-4ef3-95ff-f71f4d8482be)\n\n</details>\n\nShowcase explanation:\n1. The first time I open, highlight seems to reappear if I try to navigate down in the window\n2. Subsequent times, highlight reappears if I manually redraw nvim `:mode` or `CTRL_L`, have to press it >1 times\n\n\nMy treesitter (main branch) config, I have all parsers installed normal highlighting is no problem\n\n```lua\n        vim.api.nvim_create_autocmd(\"FileType\", {\n            callback = function(ev)\n                local success, parser = pcall(vim.treesitter.get_parser, ev.buf)\n                if success and parser then\n                    vim.treesitter.stop(ev.buf)\n                    vim.treesitter.start(ev.buf)\n                end\n            end,\n        })\n```\n\nHowever I can confirm this happens even if I disable this autocmd.\n\nI want to say in advance I apologize for such a vague bug report, but this is what I have figured out so far\n\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nI'm afraid I didn't find a consistent reproducable step, it happens after some time (30mins) using any* (ts_ls, rust_analyzer, gopls) lsp\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nShould render correctly without any user intervention\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.11.1 0.11.2\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\n-\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmac/linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\ntmux 3.5 kitty\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nthe tmux one\n\n### Installation\n\narch/extra",
